text:
Astronomers discover a formation on Mars that resembles a bear

The University of Arizona’s Lunar and Planetary Laboratory recently shared this image of several martian surface features that combine to resemble the face of a bear.
NASA/JPL-Caltech/University of Arizona https://t.co/h4PAArQoU8

text:
A Bear on Mars? Not exactly. This feature may look a bit like a bear’s face, but really it's a hill with a V-shaped collapse structure (the nose), two craters (the eyes), and a circular fracture pattern (the head). 🐻

Credit: NASA/JPL/University of Arizona https://t.co/1lrNNmWo1n
